{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"split(string:matchOptions:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib13RegexProtocolPAAE5split6string12matchOptionsSpySpys4Int8VGSgGSgSPyAHGSg_AA0B10MatchFlagsVtF","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"split","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"string"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"matchOptions"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"RegexMatchFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib15RegexMatchFlagsV"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/regexprotocol\/split(string:matchoptions:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexProtocol\/split(string:matchOptions:)"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Breaks the string on the pattern, and returns an array of the tokens."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If the pattern contains capturing parentheses, then the text for each","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the substrings will also be returned. If the pattern does not match"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"anywhere in the string, then the whole string is returned as the first","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"token.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"split","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"string"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"matchOptions","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib15RegexMatchFlagsV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexMatchFlags","text":"RegexMatchFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As a special case, the result of splitting the empty string “” is an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"empty vector, not a vector containing a single string. The reason for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this special case is that being able to represent an empty vector is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"typically more useful than consistent handling of empty elements. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you do need to represent empty elements, you’ll need to check for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"empty string before calling this function.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A pattern that can match empty strings splits ","type":"text"},{"code":"string","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" into separate"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"characters wherever it matches the empty string between characters.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For example splitting “ab c” using as a separator “\\s*”, you will get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“a”, “b” and “c”."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexProtocol"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RegexProtocol/split(string:matchOptions:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexProtocol\/split(string:matchOptions:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"split","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"matchOptions","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib15RegexMatchFlagsV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"RegexMatchFlags"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?>!"}],"title":"split(string:matchOptions:)","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/regexprotocol\/split(string:matchoptions:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Breaks the string on the pattern, and returns an arra